Name: Pulp Fiction
Directors_Cast: Quentin Tarantino John Travolta Uma Thurman Samuel L. Jackson Bruce Willis
Discription: \nThe lives of two mob hitmen a boxer a gangster and his wife and a pair of diner bandits intertwine in four tales of violence and redemption.

Name: The Amazing Spider-Man 2
Directors_Cast: Marc Webb Andrew Garfield Emma Stone Jamie Foxx Paul Giamatti
Discription: \nWhen New York is put under siege by Oscorp it is up to Spider-Man to save the city he swore to protect as well as his loved ones.

Name: The Shawshank Redemption
Directors_Cast: Frank Darabont Tim Robbins Morgan Freeman Bob Gunton William Sadler
Discription: \nTwo imprisoned men bond over a number of years finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.

Name: Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope
Directors_Cast: George Lucas Mark Hamill Harrison Ford Carrie Fisher Alec Guinness
Discription: \nLuke Skywalker joins forces with a Jedi Knight a cocky pilot a Wookiee and two droids to save the galaxy from the Empires world-destroying battle station while also attempting to rescue Princess Leia from the mysterious Darth Vader.

Name: Back to the Future
Directors_Cast: Robert Zemeckis Michael J. Fox Christopher Lloyd Lea Thompson Crispin Glover
Discription: \nMarty McFly a 17-year-old high school student is accidentally sent thirty years into the past in a time-traveling DeLorean invented by his close friend the eccentric scientist Doc Brown.

Name: The Breakfast Club
Directors_Cast: John Hughes Emilio Estevez Judd Nelson Molly Ringwald Ally Sheedy
Discription: \nFive high school students meet in Saturday detention and discover how they have a lot more in common than they thought.

Name: The Goonies
Directors_Cast: Richard Donner Sean Astin Josh Brolin Jeff Cohen Corey Feldman
Discription: \nA group of young misfits called The Goonies discover an ancient map and set out on an adventure to find a legendary pirates long-lost treasure.

Name: The Silence of the Lambs
Directors_Cast: Jonathan Demme Jodie Foster Anthony Hopkins Lawrence A. Bonney Kasi Lemmons
Discription: \nA young F.B.I. cadet must receive the help of an incarcerated and manipulative cannibal killer to help catch another serial killer a madman who skins his victims.

Name: Jurassic Park
Directors_Cast: Steven Spielberg Sam Neill Laura Dern Jeff Goldblum Richard Attenborough
Discription: \nA pragmatic paleontologist visiting an almost complete theme park is tasked with protecting a couple of kids after a power failure causes the parks cloned dinosaurs to run loose.

Name: The Lion King
Directors_Cast: Roger Allers Rob Minkoff Matthew Broderick Jeremy Irons James Earl Jones Whoopi Goldberg
Discription: \nLion prince Simba and his father are targeted by his bitter uncle who wants to ascend the throne himself.

Name: Se7en
Directors_Cast: David Fincher Morgan Freeman Brad Pitt Kevin Spacey Andrew Kevin Walker
Discription: \nTwo detectives a rookie and a veteran hunt a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his motives.

Name: Toy Story
Directors_Cast: John Lasseter Tom Hanks Tim Allen Don Rickles Jim Varney
Discription: \nA cowboy doll is profoundly threatened and jealous when a new spaceman figure supplants him as top toy in a boys room.

Name: The Big Lebowski
Directors_Cast: Joel Coen Ethan Coen Jeff Bridges John Goodman Julianne Moore Steve Buscemi
Discription: \nJeff The Dude Lebowski mistaken for a millionaire of the same name seeks restitution for his ruined rug and enlists his bowling buddies to help get it.

Name: Saving Private Ryan
Directors_Cast: Steven Spielberg Tom Hanks Matt Damon Tom Sizemore Edward Burns
Discription: \nFollowing the Normandy Landings a group of U.S. soldiers go behind enemy lines to retrieve a paratrooper whose brothers have been killed in action.

Name: Fight Club
Directors_Cast: David Fincher Brad Pitt Edward Norton Meat Loaf Zach Grenier
Discription: \nAn insomniac office worker and a devil-may-care soap maker form an underground fight club that evolves into much more.

Name: The Matrix
Directors_Cast: Lana Wachowski Lilly Wachowski Keanu Reeves Laurence Fishburne Carrie-Anne Moss Hugo Weaving
Discription: \nWhen a beautiful stranger leads computer hacker Neo to a forbidding underworld he discovers the shocking truth--the life he knows is the elaborate deception of an evil cyber-intelligence.

Name: Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace
Directors_Cast: George Lucas Ewan McGregor Liam Neeson Natalie Portman Jake Lloyd
Discription: \nTwo Jedi escape a hostile blockade to find allies and come across a young boy who may bring balance to the Force but the long dormant Sith resurface to claim their original glory.

Name: Gladiator
Directors_Cast: Ridley Scott Russell Crowe Joaquin Phoenix Connie Nielsen Oliver Reed
Discription: \nA former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

Name: X-Men
Directors_Cast: Bryan Singer Patrick Stewart Hugh Jackman Ian McKellen Famke Janssen
Discription: \nIn a world where mutants evolved super-powered humans exist and are discriminated against two groups form for an inevitable clash: the supremacist Brotherhood and the pacifist X-Men.

Name: Harry Potter and the Sorcerers Stone
Directors_Cast: Chris Columbus Daniel Radcliffe Rupert Grint Richard Harris Maggie Smith
Discription: \nAn orphaned boy enrolls in a school of wizardry where he learns the truth about himself his family and the terrible evil that haunts the magical world.

Name: The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring
Directors_Cast: Peter Jackson Elijah Wood Ian McKellen Orlando Bloom Sean Bean
Discription: \nA meek Hobbit from the Shire and eight companions set out on a journey to destroy the powerful One Ring and save Middle-earth from the Dark Lord Sauron.

Name: The Lord of the Rings: The Two Towers
Directors_Cast: Peter Jackson Elijah Wood Ian McKellen Viggo Mortensen Orlando Bloom
Discription: \nWhile Frodo and Sam edge closer to Mordor with the help of the shifty Gollum the divided fellowship makes a stand against Saurons new ally Saruman and his hordes of Isengard.

Name: xXx
Directors_Cast: Rob Cohen Vin Diesel Asia Argento Marton Csokas Samuel L. Jackson
Discription: \nAn extreme sports athlete Xander Cage is recruited by the government on a special mission.

Name: Finding Nemo
Directors_Cast: Andrew Stanton Lee Unkrich Albert Brooks Ellen DeGeneres Alexander Gould Willem Dafoe
Discription: \nAfter his son is captured in the Great Barrier Reef and taken to Sydney a timid clownfish sets out on a journey to bring him home.

Name: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
Directors_Cast: Peter Jackson Elijah Wood Viggo Mortensen Ian McKellen Orlando Bloom
Discription: \nGandalf and Aragorn lead the World of Men against Saurons army to draw his gaze from Frodo and Sam as they approach Mount Doom with the One Ring.

Name: Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy
Directors_Cast: Adam McKay Will Ferrell Christina Applegate Steve Carell Paul Rudd
Discription: \nRon Burgundy is San Diegos top-rated newsman in the male-dominated broadcasting of the 1970s but thats all about to change for Ron and his cronies when an ambitious woman is hired as a new anchor.

Name: Mean Girls
Directors_Cast: Mark Waters Lindsay Lohan Jonathan Bennett Rachel McAdams Tina Fey
Discription: \nCady Heron is a hit with The Plastics the A-list girl clique at her new school until she makes the mistake of falling for Aaron Samuels the ex-boyfriend of alpha Plastic Regina George.

Name: Sin City
Directors_Cast: Frank Miller Quentin Tarantino Robert Rodriguez Mickey Rourke Clive Owen Bruce Willis Jessica Alba
Discription: \nAn exploration of the dark and miserable Basin City and three of its residents all of whom are caught up in violent corruption.

Name: Star Wars: Episode III - Revenge of the Sith
Directors_Cast: George Lucas Hayden Christensen Natalie Portman Ewan McGregor Samuel L. Jackson
Discription: \nThree years into the Clone Wars the Jedi rescue Palpatine from Count Dooku. As Obi-Wan pursues a new threat Anakin acts as a double agent between the Jedi Council and Palpatine and is lured into a sinister plan to rule the galaxy.

Name: Batman Begins
Directors_Cast: Christopher Nolan Christian Bale Michael Caine Ken Watanabe Liam Neeson
Discription: \nAfter training with his mentor Batman begins his fight to free crime-ridden Gotham City from corruption.

Name: The Departed
Directors_Cast: Martin Scorsese Leonardo DiCaprio Matt Damon Jack Nicholson Mark Wahlberg
Discription: \nAn undercover cop and a mole in the police attempt to identify each other while infiltrating an Irish gang in South Boston.

Name: The Prestige
Directors_Cast: Christopher Nolan Christian Bale Hugh Jackman Scarlett Johansson Michael Caine
Discription: \nAfter a tragic accident two stage magicians engage in a battle to create the ultimate illusion while sacrificing everything they have to outwit each other.

Name: V for Vendetta
Directors_Cast: James McTeigue Hugo Weaving Natalie Portman Rupert Graves Stephen Rea
Discription: \nIn a future British tyranny a shadowy freedom fighter known only by the alias of V plots to overthrow it with the help of a young woman.

Name: Casino Royale
Directors_Cast: Martin Campbell Daniel Craig Eva Green Judi Dench Jeffrey Wright
Discription: \nAfter earning 00 status and a licence to kill Secret Agent James Bond sets out on his first mission as 007. Bond must defeat a private banker funding terrorists in a high-stakes game of poker at Casino Royale Montenegro.

Name: Transformers
Directors_Cast: Michael Bay Shia LaBeouf Megan Fox Josh Duhamel Tyrese Gibson
Discription: \nAn ancient struggle between two Cybertronian races the heroic Autobots and the evil Decepticons comes to Earth with a clue to the ultimate power held by a teenager.

Name: The Dark Knight
Directors_Cast: Christopher Nolan Christian Bale Heath Ledger Aaron Eckhart Michael Caine
Discription: \nWhen the menace known as the Joker wreaks havoc and chaos on the people of Gotham Batman must accept one of the greatest psychological and physical tests of his ability to fight injustice.

Name: Iron Man
Directors_Cast: Jon Favreau Robert Downey Jr. Gwyneth Paltrow Terrence Howard Jeff Bridges
Discription: \nAfter being held captive in an Afghan cave billionaire engineer Tony Stark creates a unique weaponized suit of armor to fight evil.

Name: Quantum of Solace
Directors_Cast: Marc Forster Daniel Craig Olga Kurylenko Mathieu Amalric Judi Dench
Discription: \nJames Bond descends into mystery as he tries to stop a mysterious organisation from eliminating a countrys most valuable resource.

Name: Tropic Thunder
Directors_Cast: Ben Stiller Ben Stiller Jack Black Robert Downey Jr. Jeff Kahn
Discription: \nThrough a series of freak occurrences a group of actors shooting a big-budget war movie are forced to become the soldiers they are portraying.

Name: G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra
Directors_Cast: Stephen Sommers Dennis Quaid Channing Tatum Marlon Wayans Adewale Akinnuoye-Agbaje
Discription: \nAn elite military unit comprised of special operatives known as G.I. Joe operating out of The Pit takes on an evil organization led by a notorious arms dealer.

Name: The Hangover
Directors_Cast: Todd Phillips Zach Galifianakis Bradley Cooper Justin Bartha Ed Helms
Discription: \nThree buddies wake up from a bachelor party in Las Vegas with no memory of the previous night and the bachelor missing. They make their way around the city in order to find their friend before his wedding.

Name: Inglourious Basterds
Directors_Cast: Quentin Tarantino Brad Pitt Diane Kruger Eli Roth Mélanie Laurent
Discription: \nIn Nazi-occupied France during World War II a plan to assassinate Nazi leaders by a group of Jewish U.S. soldiers coincides with a theatre owners vengeful plans for the same.

Name: Star Trek
Directors_Cast: J.J. Abrams Chris Pine Zachary Quinto Simon Pegg Leonard Nimoy
Discription: \nThe brash James T. Kirk tries to live up to his fathers legacy with Mr. Spock keeping him in check as a vengeful Romulan from the future creates black holes to destroy the Federation one planet at a time.

Name: Taken
Directors_Cast: Pierre Morel Liam Neeson Maggie Grace Famke Janssen Leland Orser
Discription: \nA retired CIA agent travels across Europe and relies on his old skills to save his estranged daughter who has been kidnapped while on a trip to Paris.

Name: Up
Directors_Cast: Pete Docter Bob Peterson Edward Asner Jordan Nagai John Ratzenberger Christopher Plummer
Discription: \n78-year-old Carl Fredricksen travels to Paradise Falls in his house equipped with balloons inadvertently taking a young stowaway.

Name: X-Men Origins: Wolverine
Directors_Cast: Gavin Hood Hugh Jackman Liev Schreiber Ryan Reynolds Danny Huston
Discription: \nThe early years of James Logan featuring his rivalry with his brother Victor Creed his service in the special forces team Weapon X and his experimentation into the metal-lined mutant Wolverine.

Name: Zombieland
Directors_Cast: Ruben Fleischer Jesse Eisenberg Emma Stone Woody Harrelson Abigail Breslin
Discription: \nA shy student trying to reach his family in Ohio a gun-toting bruiser in search or the last Twinkie and a pair of sisters striving to get to an amusement park join forces in a trek across a zombie-filled America.

Directors_Cast: Roland Emmerich John Cusack Thandiwe Newton Chiwetel Ejiofor Amanda Peet
Discription: \nA frustrated writer struggles to keep his family alive when a series of global catastrophes threatens to annihilate mankind.

Name: Avatar
Directors_Cast: James Cameron Sam Worthington Zoe Saldana Sigourney Weaver Michelle Rodriguez
Discription: \nA paraplegic Marine dispatched to the moon Pandora on a unique mission becomes torn between following his orders and protecting the world he feels is his home.

Name: Despicable Me
Directors_Cast: Pierre Coffin Chris Renaud Steve Carell Jason Segel Russell Brand Julie Andrews
Discription: \nWhen a criminal mastermind uses a trio of orphan girls as pawns for a grand scheme he finds their love is profoundly changing him for the better.

Name: Grown Ups
Directors_Cast: Dennis Dugan Adam Sandler Salma Hayek Kevin James Chris Rock
Discription: \nAfter their high school basketball coach passes away five good friends and former teammates reunite for a Fourth of July holiday weekend.

Name: How to Train Your Dragon
Directors_Cast: Dean DeBlois Chris Sanders Jay Baruchel Gerard Butler Christopher Mintz-Plasse Craig Ferguson
Discription: \nA hapless young Viking who aspires to hunt dragons becomes the unlikely friend of a young dragon himself and learns there may be more to the creatures than he assumed.

Name: Inception
Directors_Cast: Christopher Nolan Leonardo DiCaprio Joseph Gordon-Levitt Elliot Page Ken Watanabe
Discription: \nA thief who steals corporate secrets through the use of dream-sharing technology is given the inverse task of planting an idea into the mind of a C.E.O.

Name: Iron Man 2
Directors_Cast: Jon Favreau Robert Downey Jr. Mickey Rourke Gwyneth Paltrow Don Cheadle
Discription: \nWith the world now aware of his identity as Iron Man Tony Stark must contend with both his declining health and a vengeful mad man with ties to his fathers legacy.

Name: Kick-Ass
Directors_Cast: Matthew Vaughn Aaron Taylor-Johnson Nicolas Cage Chloë Grace Moretz Garrett M. Brown
Discription: \nDave Lizewski is an unnoticed high school student and comic book fan who one day decides to become a superhero even though he has no powers training or meaningful reason to do so.

Name: RED
Directors_Cast: Robert Schwentke Bruce Willis Helen Mirren Morgan Freeman Mary-Louise Parker
Discription: \nWhen his peaceful life is threatened by a high-tech assassin former black-ops agent Frank Moses reassembles his old team in a last-ditch effort to survive and uncover his assailants.

Name: Shutter Island
Directors_Cast: Martin Scorsese Leonardo DiCaprio Emily Mortimer Mark Ruffalo Ben Kingsley
Discription: \nIn 1954 a U.S. Marshal investigates the disappearance of a murderer who escaped from a hospital for the criminally insane.

Name: TRON: Legacy
Directors_Cast: Joseph Kosinski Jeff Bridges Garrett Hedlund Olivia Wilde Bruce Boxleitner
Discription: \nThe son of a virtual world designer goes looking for his father and ends up inside the digital world that his father designed. He meets his fathers corrupted creation and a unique ally who was born inside the digital world.

Name: Toy Story 3
Directors_Cast: Lee Unkrich Tom Hanks Tim Allen Joan Cusack Ned Beatty
Discription: \nThe toys are mistakenly delivered to a day-care center instead of the attic right before Andy leaves for college and its up to Woody to convince the other toys that they werent abandoned and to return home.

Name: Drive
Directors_Cast: Nicolas Winding Refn Ryan Gosling Carey Mulligan Bryan Cranston Albert Brooks
Discription: \nA mysterious Hollywood stuntman and mechanic moonlights as a getaway driver and finds himself in trouble when he helps out his neighbor.

Name: Fast Five
Directors_Cast: Justin Lin Vin Diesel Paul Walker Dwayne Johnson Jordana Brewster
Discription: \nDominic Toretto and his crew of street racers plan a massive heist to buy their freedom while in the sights of a powerful Brazilian drug lord and a dangerous federal agent.

Name: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
Directors_Cast: David Yates Daniel Radcliffe Emma Watson Rupert Grint Michael Gambon
Discription: \nHarry Ron and Hermione search for Voldemorts remaining Horcruxes in their effort to destroy the Dark Lord as the final battle rages on at Hogwarts.

Name: Limitless
Directors_Cast: Neil Burger Bradley Cooper Anna Friel Abbie Cornish Robert De Niro
Discription: \nWith the help of a mysterious pill that enables the user to access 100% of his brains abilities a struggling writer becomes a financial wizard but it also puts him in a new world with many dangers.

Name: Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides
Directors_Cast: Rob Marshall Johnny Depp Penélope Cruz Ian McShane Geoffrey Rush
Discription: \nJack Sparrow and Barbossa embark on a quest to find the elusive fountain of youth only to discover that Blackbeard and his daughter are after it too.

Name: X-Men: First Class
Directors_Cast: Matthew Vaughn James McAvoy Michael Fassbender Jennifer Lawrence Kevin Bacon
Discription: \nIn the 1960s superpowered humans Charles Xavier and Erik Lensherr work together to find others like them but Eriks vengeful pursuit of an ambitious mutant who ruined his life causes a schism to divide them.

Name: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
Directors_Cast: David Fincher Daniel Craig Rooney Mara Christopher Plummer Stellan Skarsgård
Discription: \nJournalist Mikael Blomkvist is aided in his search for a woman who has been missing for forty years by Lisbeth Salander a young computer hacker.

Name: The Help
Directors_Cast: Tate Taylor Emma Stone Viola Davis Octavia Spencer Bryce Dallas Howard
Discription: \nAn aspiring author during the civil rights movement of the 1960s decides to write a book detailing the African American maids point of view on the white families for which they work and the hardships they go through on a daily basis.

Name: In Time
Directors_Cast: Andrew Niccol Justin Timberlake Amanda Seyfried Cillian Murphy Olivia Wilde
Discription: \nIn a future where people stop aging at 25 but are engineered to live only one more year having the means to buy your way out of the situation is a shot at immortal youth. Here Will Salas finds himself accused of murder and on the run with a hostage - a connection that becomes an important part of the way against the system.

Name: 21 Jump Street
Directors_Cast: Phil Lord Christopher Miller Jonah Hill Channing Tatum Ice Cube Brie Larson
Discription: \nA pair of underachieving cops are sent back to a local high school to blend in and bring down a synthetic drug ring.

Name: The Amazing Spider-Man
Directors_Cast: Marc Webb Andrew Garfield Emma Stone Rhys Ifans Irrfan Khan
Discription: \nAfter Peter Parker is bitten by a genetically altered spider he gains newfound spider-like powers and ventures out to save the city from the machinations of a mysterious reptilian foe.

Name: American Reunion
Directors_Cast: Jon Hurwitz Hayden Schlossberg Jason Biggs Alyson Hannigan Seann William Scott Chris Klein
Discription: \nJim Michelle Stifler and their friends reunite in East Great Falls Michigan for their high school reunion.

Name: The Avengers
Directors_Cast: Joss Whedon Robert Downey Jr. Chris Evans Scarlett Johansson Jeremy Renner
Discription: \nEarths mightiest heroes must come together and learn to fight as a team if they are going to stop the mischievous Loki and his alien army from enslaving humanity.

Name: Battleship
Directors_Cast: Peter Berg Alexander Skarsgård Brooklyn Decker Liam Neeson Rihanna
Discription: \nA fleet of ships is forced to do battle with an armada of unknown origins in order to discover and thwart their destructive goals.

Name: The Bourne Legacy
Directors_Cast: Tony Gilroy Jeremy Renner Rachel Weisz Edward Norton Scott Glenn
Discription: \nAn expansion of the universe from Robert Ludlums novels centered on a new hero whose stakes have been triggered by the events of the previous three films.

Name: Brave
Directors_Cast: Mark Andrews Brenda Chapman Steve Purcell Kelly Macdonald Billy Connolly Emma Thompson Julie Walters
Discription: \nDetermined to make her own path in life Princess Merida Kelly Macdonald defies a custom that brings chaos to her kingdom. Granted one wish Merida must rely on her bravery and her archery skills to undo a beastly curse.

Name: The Cabin in the Woods
Directors_Cast: Drew Goddard Kristen Connolly Chris Hemsworth Anna Hutchison Fran Kranz
Discription: \nFive friends go for a break at a remote cabin where they get more than they bargained for discovering the truth behind the cabin in the woods.

Name: The Campaign
Directors_Cast: Jay Roach Will Ferrell Zach Galifianakis Jason Sudeikis Dylan McDermott
Discription: \nAn incumbent Representative embroiled in personal scandal faces a no-holds-barred challenge from a naive newcomer funded by two unscrupulous billionaire lobbyist brothers.

Name: Cloud Atlas
Directors_Cast: Tom Tykwer Lana Wachowski Lilly Wachowski Tom Hanks Halle Berry Hugh Grant Hugo Weaving
Discription: \nAn exploration of how the actions of individual lives impact one another in the past present and future as one soul is shaped from a killer into a hero and an act of kindness ripples across centuries to inspire a revolution.

Name: The Dark Knight Rises
Directors_Cast: Christopher Nolan Christian Bale Tom Hardy Anne Hathaway Gary Oldman
Discription: \nEight years after the Jokers reign of anarchy Batman with the help of the enigmatic Catwoman is forced from his exile to save Gotham City from the brutal guerrilla terrorist Bane.

Name: Dark Shadows
Directors_Cast: Tim Burton Johnny Depp Michelle Pfeiffer Eva Green Helena Bonham Carter
Discription: \nAn imprisoned vampire Barnabas Collins is set free and returns to his ancestral home where his dysfunctional descendants are in need of his protection.

Name: Django Unchained
Directors_Cast: Quentin Tarantino Jamie Foxx Christoph Waltz Leonardo DiCaprio Kerry Washington
Discription: \nWith the help of a German bounty-hunter a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal plantation-owner in Mississippi.

Name: Dredd
Directors_Cast: Pete Travis Karl Urban Olivia Thirlby Lena Headey Rachel Wood
Discription: \nIn a violent futuristic city where the police have the authority to act as judge jury and executioner a cop teams with a trainee to take down a gang that deals the reality-altering drug SLO-MO.

Name: End of Watch
Directors_Cast: David Ayer Jake Gyllenhaal Michael Peña Anna Kendrick America Ferrera
Discription: \nShot documentary-style this film follows the daily grind of two young police officers in LA who are partners and friends and what happens when they meet criminal forces greater than themselves.

Name: The Expendables 2
Directors_Cast: Simon West Sylvester Stallone Liam Hemsworth Randy Couture Jean-Claude Van Damme
Discription: \nMr. Church reunites the Expendables for what should be an easy paycheck but when one of their men is murdered on the job their quest for revenge puts them deep in enemy territory and up against an unexpected threat.

Name: Flight
Directors_Cast: Robert Zemeckis Denzel Washington Nadine Velazquez Don Cheadle John Goodman
Discription: \nAn airline pilot saves almost all his passengers on his malfunctioning airliner which eventually crashed but an investigation into the accident reveals something troubling.

Name: The Guilt Trip
Directors_Cast: Anne Fletcher Barbra Streisand Seth Rogen Julene Renee Zabryna Guevara
Discription: \nAs inventor Andy Brewster is about to embark on the road trip of a lifetime a quick stop at his moms house turns into an unexpected cross-country voyage with her along for the ride.

Name: Here Comes the Boom
Directors_Cast: Frank Coraci Kevin James Salma Hayek Henry Winkler Greg Germann
Discription: \nA high-school biology teacher looks to become a successful mixed martial arts fighter in an effort to raise money to prevent extracurricular activities from being axed at his cash-strapped school.

Name: The Hobbit: An Unexpected Journey
Directors_Cast: Peter Jackson Martin Freeman Ian McKellen Richard Armitage Andy Serkis
Discription: \nA reluctant Hobbit Bilbo Baggins sets out to the Lonely Mountain with a spirited group of dwarves to reclaim their mountain home and the gold within it from the dragon Smaug.

Name: Hotel Transylvania
Directors_Cast: Genndy Tartakovsky Adam Sandler Kevin James Andy Samberg Selena Gomez
Discription: \nDracula who operates a high-end resort away from the human world goes into overprotective mode when a boy discovers the resort and falls for the counts teenaged daughter.

Name: Jack Reacher
Directors_Cast: Christopher McQuarrie Tom Cruise Rosamund Pike Richard Jenkins Werner Herzog
Discription: \nA homicide investigator digs deeper into a case involving a trained military sniper who shot five random victims.

Name: John Carter
Directors_Cast: Andrew Stanton Taylor Kitsch Lynn Collins Willem Dafoe Samantha Morton
Discription: \nTransported to Barsoom a Civil War vet discovers a barren planet seemingly inhabited by 12-foot tall barbarians. Finding himself prisoner of these creatures he escapes only to encounter Woola and a princess in desperate need of a savior.

Name: Killing Them Softly
Directors_Cast: Andrew Dominik Brad Pitt Ray Liotta Richard Jenkins Scoot McNairy
Discription: \nJackie Cogan is an enforcer hired to restore order after three dumb guys rob a Mob protected card game causing the local criminal economy to collapse.

Name: Lawless
Directors_Cast: John Hillcoat Tom Hardy Shia LaBeouf Guy Pearce Jason Clarke
Discription: \nSet in Depression-era Franklin County Virginia a trio of bootlegging brothers are threatened by a new special deputy and other authorities angling for a cut of their profits.

Name: Life of Pi
Directors_Cast: Ang Lee Suraj Sharma Irrfan Khan Adil Hussain Tabu
Discription: \nA young man who survives a disaster at sea is hurtled into an epic journey of adventure and discovery. While cast away he forms an unexpected connection with another survivor: a fearsome Bengal tiger.

Name: Looper
Directors_Cast: Rian Johnson Joseph Gordon-Levitt Bruce Willis Emily Blunt Paul Dano
Discription: \nIn 2074 when the mob wants to get rid of someone the target is sent into the past where a hired gun awaits - someone like Joe - who one day learns the mob wants to close the loop by sending back Joes future self for assassination.

Name: Magic Mike
Directors_Cast: Steven Soderbergh Channing Tatum Alex Pettyfer Olivia Munn Matthew McConaughey
Discription: \nA male stripper teaches a younger performer how to party pick up women and make easy money.

Name: Man on a Ledge
Directors_Cast: Asger Leth Sam Worthington Elizabeth Banks Jamie Bell Mandy Gonzalez
Discription: \nAs a police psychologist works to talk down an ex-con who is threatening to jump from a Manhattan hotel rooftop the biggest diamond heist ever committed is in motion.

Name: The Man with the Iron Fists
Directors_Cast: RZA Russell Crowe Cung Le Lucy Liu RZA
Discription: \nOn the hunt for a fabled treasure of gold a band of warriors assassins and a rogue British soldier descend upon a village in feudal China where a humble blacksmith looks to defend himself and his fellow villagers.

Name: The Master
Directors_Cast: Paul Thomas Anderson Philip Seymour Hoffman Joaquin Phoenix Amy Adams Jesse Plemons
Discription: \nA Naval veteran arrives home from war unsettled and uncertain of his future - until he is tantalized by the Cause and its charismatic leader.

Name: Men in Black 3
Directors_Cast: Barry Sonnenfeld Will Smith Tommy Lee Jones Josh Brolin Jemaine Clement
Discription: \nAgent J travels in time to M.I.B.s early days in 1969 to stop an alien from assassinating his friend Agent K and changing history.

Name: Parental Guidance
Directors_Cast: Andy Fickman Billy Crystal Bette Midler Marisa Tomei Tom Everett Scott
Discription: \nArtie and Diane agree to look after their three grandkids when their type-A helicopter parents need to leave town for work. Problems arise when the kids 21st-century behavior collides with Artie and Dianes old-school methods.

Name: Project X
Directors_Cast: Nima Nourizadeh Thomas Mann Oliver Cooper Jonathan Daniel Brown Dax Flame
Discription: \n3 high school seniors throw a birthday party to make a name for themselves. As the night progresses things spiral out of control as word of the party spreads.

Name: Prometheus
Directors_Cast: Ridley Scott Noomi Rapace Logan Marshall-Green Michael Fassbender Charlize Theron
Discription: \nFollowing clues to the origin of mankind a team finds a structure on a distant moon but they soon realize they are not alone.

Name: Red Dawn
Directors_Cast: Dan Bradley Chris Hemsworth Isabel Lucas Josh Hutcherson Josh Peck
Discription: \nA group of teenagers look to save their town from an invasion of North Korean soldiers.

Name: Rise of the Guardians
Directors_Cast: Peter Ramsey Hugh Jackman Alec Baldwin Isla Fisher Chris Pine
Discription: \nWhen the evil spirit Pitch launches an assault on Earth the Immortal Guardians team up to protect the innocence of children all around the world.

Name: Savages
Directors_Cast: Oliver Stone Aaron Taylor-Johnson Taylor Kitsch Blake Lively Benicio Del Toro
Discription: \nPot growers Ben and Chon face off against the Mexican drug cartel who kidnapped their shared girlfriend.

Name: Seven Psychopaths
Directors_Cast: Martin McDonagh Colin Farrell Woody Harrelson Sam Rockwell Christopher Walken
Discription: \nA struggling screenwriter inadvertently becomes entangled in the Los Angeles criminal underworld after his oddball friends kidnap a gangsters beloved Shih Tzu.

Name: Sinister
Directors_Cast: Scott Derrickson Ethan Hawke Juliet Rylance James Ransone Fred Thompson
Discription: \nWashed-up true crime writer Ellison Oswalt finds a box of super 8 home movies in his new home that suggest the murder that he is currently researching is the work of a serial killer whose work dates back to the 1960s.

Name: Skyfall
Directors_Cast: Sam Mendes Daniel Craig Javier Bardem Naomie Harris Judi Dench
Discription: \nJames Bonds loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. When MI6 comes under attack 007 must track down and destroy the threat no matter how personal the cost.

Name: Snow White and the Huntsman
Directors_Cast: Rupert Sanders Kristen Stewart Chris Hemsworth Charlize Theron Sam Claflin
Discription: \nIn a twist to the fairy tale the Huntsman ordered to take Snow White into the woods to be killed winds up becoming her protector and mentor in a quest to vanquish the Evil Queen.

Name: Taken 2
Directors_Cast: Olivier Megaton Liam Neeson Famke Janssen Maggie Grace Leland Orser
Discription: \nIn Istanbul retired CIA operative Bryan Mills and his wife are taken hostage by the father of a kidnapper Mills killed while rescuing his daughter.

Name: Ted

Discription: \nTChalla heir to the hidden but advanced kingdom of Wakanda must step forward to lead his people into a new future and must confront a challenger from his countrys past.

Discription: \nCallum Lynch explores the memories of his ancestor Aguilar de Nerha and gains the skills of a Master Assassin before taking on the secret Templar society.

Discription: \nWhen John Connor leader of the human resistance sends Sgt. Kyle Reese back to 1984 to protect Sarah Connor and safeguard the future an unexpected turn of events creates a fractured timeline.

Name: Poltergeist

Name: Tomorrowland

Discription: \nBound by a shared destiny a teen bursting with scientific curiosity and a former boy-genius inventor embark on a mission to unearth the secrets of a place somewhere in time and space that exists in their collective memory.

Name: The Revenant
Directors_Cast: Alejandro G. Iñárritu Leonardo DiCaprio Tom Hardy Will Poulter Domhnall Gleeson
Discription: \nA frontiersman on a fur trading expedition in the 1820s fights for survival after being mauled by a bear and left for dead by members of his own hunting team.

Name: The Good Dinosaur
Directors_Cast: Peter Sohn Jeffrey Wright Frances McDormand Maleah Nipay-Padilla Ryan Teeple
Discription: \nIn a world where dinosaurs and humans live side-by-side an Apatosaurus named Arlo makes an unlikely human friend.

Directors_Cast: Peter Jackson Jamie Bell Andy Serkis

Name: Mission: Impossible - Rogue Nation
Directors_Cast: Christopher McQuarrie Tom Cruise Rebecca Ferguson Jeremy Renner Simon Pegg
Discription: \nEthan and his team take on their most impossible mission yet when they have to eradicate an international rogue organization as highly skilled as they are and committed to destroying the IMF.

Name: Independence Day: Resurgence
Directors_Cast: Roland Emmerich Liam Hemsworth Jeff Goldblum Bill Pullman Maika Monroe
Discription: \nTwo decades after the first Independence Day invasion Earth is faced with a new extra-Solar threat. But will mankinds new space defenses be enough?

Name: Pirates of the Caribbean: Dead Men Tell No Tales
Directors_Cast: Joachim Rønning Espen Sandberg Johnny Depp Geoffrey Rush Javier Bardem Orlando Bloom
Discription: \nCaptain Jack Sparrow is pursued by old rival Captain Salazar and a crew of deadly ghosts who have escaped from the Devils Triangle. Theyre determined to kill every pirate at sea...notably Jack.

Name: Warcraft
Directors_Cast: Duncan Jones Travis Fimmel Paula Patton Ben Foster Dominic Cooper
Discription: \nAs an Orc horde invades the planet Azeroth using a magic portal a few human heroes and dissenting Orcs must attempt to stop the true evil behind this war.

Name: The Mummy

Discription: \nAn ancient Egyptian princess is awakened from her crypt beneath the desert bringing with her malevolence grown over millennia and terrors that defy human comprehension.

Name: Deadpool
Directors_Cast: Tim Miller Ryan Reynolds Morena Baccarin T.J. Miller Ed Skrein
Discription: \nA wisecracking mercenary gets experimented on and becomes immortal but ugly and sets out to track down the man who ruined his looks.

Name: Steve Jobs
Directors_Cast: Danny Boyle Michael Fassbender Kate Winslet Seth Rogen Jeff Daniels
Discription: \n Steve Jobs  takes us behind the scenes of the digital revolution to paint a portrait of the man at its epicenter. The story unfolds backstage at three iconic product launches ending in 1998 with the unveiling of the iMac.

Name: Chappie
Directors_Cast: Neill Blomkamp Sharlto Copley Dev Patel Hugh Jackman Sigourney Weaver
Discription: \nIn the near future crime is patrolled by a mechanized police force. When one police droid Chappie is stolen and given new programming he becomes the first robot with the ability to think and feel for himself.

Name: Lange
Directors_Cast: Leslie Dektor

Name: Spectre
Directors_Cast: Sam Mendes Daniel Craig Christoph Waltz Léa Seydoux Ralph Fiennes
Discription: \nA cryptic message from James Bonds past sends him on a trail to uncover the existence of a sinister organisation named SPECTRE. With a new threat dawning Bond learns the terrible truth about the author of all his pain in his most recent missions.

Name: Brooklyn
Directors_Cast: John Crowley Saoirse Ronan Emory Cohen Domhnall Gleeson Jim Broadbent

Name: Aquaman
Directors_Cast: James Wan Jason Momoa Amber Heard Willem Dafoe Patrick Wilson

Name: Live by Night

Discription: \nA group of Boston-bred gangsters set up shop in balmy Florida during the Prohibition era facing off against the competition and the Ku Klux Klan.

Name: The Neon Demon

Discription: \nLife for the residents of a tower block begins to run out of control.

Name: Sausage Party
Directors_Cast: Greg Tiernan Conrad Vernon Seth Rogen Kristen Wiig Jonah Hill Alistair Abell
Discription: \nA sausage strives to discover the truth about his existence.

Name: True Story
Directors_Cast: Rupert Goold James Franco Jonah Hill Felicity Jones Maria Dizzia
Discription: \nWhen disgraced New York Times reporter Michael Finkel meets accused killer Christian Longo - who has taken on Finkels identity - his investigation morphs into a game of cat-and-mouse.

Name: Fantastic Four

Name: Justice League

Name: Love the Coopers
